Final shortest distances from \(A\): \(B=4\), \(C=2\), \(D=9\), \(E=5\), \(F=12\).
The shortest path to \(F\) is \(A \to C \to E \to F\) with total weight \(2+3+7=12\). This means Dijkstra is not merely producing distances one by one. It is building a growing tree of already-certified shortest paths.

Use the stepper to watch the shortest-path tree grow one certified vertex at a time.


